{
  "texts": [
    "Elucidating the relationship between non-coding regulatory element sequences and gene expression is crucial for understanding gene regulation and genetic variation.",
    "We explored this link with the training of interpretable deep learning models predicting gene expression profiles from gene flanking regions of the plant species Arabidopsis thaliana, Solanum lycopersicum, Sorghum bicolor, and Zea mays.",
    "With over 80% accuracy, our models enabled predictive feature selection, highlighting e.g.",
    "the significant role of UTR regions in determining gene expression levels.",
    "The models demonstrated remarkable cross-species performance, effectively identifying both conserved and species-specific regulatory sequence features and their predictive power for gene expression."
  ]
}